                    <sense xml:id="Tmain" xml:lang="en" source="#traces"> <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez"><quote> nǝwāy </quote></cit> <gramGrp> <pos expand="Substantivum">subst.</pos> </gramGrp>, a unit of mass <foreign xml:lang="gez">ወወሀበ፡ ሎሙ፡ ቤዛሆሙ፡ መሐመድሃ፡ ወልዶ፡ ለኢማም፡ አሕመድ። ወተውሳከ፡ ውእቱ፡ እልፈ፡ ንዋየ።</foreign> ‘<cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><quote> He gave for their ransom Mäḫammäd, son of Imām ʾAḥmäd and in addition a thousand Nǝway. </quote></cit>’ <bibl><ptr target="bm:Solomon2019GalawdewosI"/><citedRange unit="page"> 40 § 67 (ed.)</citedRange></bibl>, <bibl><ptr target="bm:Solomon2019GalawdewosII"/><citedRange unit="page"> 23 § 67 (tr.)</citedRange></bibl> (‘<cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez"><quote> Nǝway </quote></cit> is an Arab unit of weight equivalent of two thirds ounces of metal gold which means g 2.942. Cf. <bibl><ptr target="bm:Pereira1888Minas"/><citedRange unit="page"> 61</citedRange></bibl>.’ <bibl><ptr target="bm:Solomon2019GalawdewosII"/><citedRange unit="page"> 23 n. 101</citedRange></bibl>) <nd/> </sense>
